Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-total-gas-q3fy24-results-net-profit-rises-18-to-rs-176-64-crore-124013000723_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-total-gas-q3fy24-results-net-profit-rises-18-to-rs-176-64-crore-124013000723_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Jio%E2%80%99s%20new%20platform%20aims%20to%20integrate%20AI%20into%20telecom%20network%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706617914000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107265611%2Cimgsize-74262.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fjio-brain-integrating-ai-into-telecom-network-jio-platforms%2Farticleshow%2F107265661.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jio%20Platforms%2C%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20Reliance%20Industries%2C%20has%20developed%20an%20innovative%20AI%20platform%20called%20Jio%20Brain.%20Jio%20Brain%20integrates%20machine%20learning%20capabilities%20in%20telecom%20and%20enterprise%20networks%20without%20the%20need%20for%20extensive%20transformation.%20It%20offers%20over%20500%20APIs%20to%20create%20ML-enabled%20services%20for%20images%2C%20videos%2C%20text%2C%20documents%2C%20and%20speech.%20The%20platform%20facilitates%20the%20creation%20of%20new%205G%20services%2C%20enterprise%20transformation%2C%20network%20optimization%2C%20and%20sets%20the%20foundation%20for%206G%20development.%20Jio%20Platforms%20aims%20to%20collaborate%20with%20AI%2FML%20researchers%20to%20scale%20the%20Jio%20Brain%20innovation%20ecosystem.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bharatiya%20Nyay%20Sanhita%3A%20Decolonising%20or%20Reinforcing%20Colonial%20Ideas%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11180259%2FUneven.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202023%2C%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%20enacted%20three%20new%20criminal%20codes%E2%80%94the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(%E2%80%98BNS%E2%80%99)%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagrik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20(%E2%80%98BNSS%E2%80%99)%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20(%E2%80%98BSA%E2%80%99)%E2%80%94to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%20(%E2%80%98IPC%E2%80%99)%2C%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C%201973%20(%E2%80%98CrPC%E2%80%99)%2C%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%20(%E2%80%98IEA%E2%80%99)%2C%20respectively.%20The%20Bills%20received%20Presidential%20assent%2C%20and%20were%20published%20in%20the%20Official%20Gazette%20on%20December%2025%2C%202023.%20The%20date%20on%20which%20they%20will%20come%20into%20force%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20notified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stated%20aim%20of%20these%20three%20legislations%20is%20to%20%E2%80%98decolonise%E2%80%99%20criminal%20laws%20of%20the%20British%20era.%20The%20Union%20Government%20has%20repeatedly%20invoked%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20decolonisation%2C%20justice%2C%20and%20citizen-centric%20laws%20to%20justify%20this%20legal%20reform%20project.%20To%20assess%20whether%20the%20new%20laws%20succeed%20in%20this%20aim%2C%20we%20must%20first%20articulate%20what%20was%20colonial%20about%20these%20three%20legislations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20piece%20focuses%20on%20the%20BNS%2C%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20IPC.%20It%20analyses%20how%20the%20bill%20falls%20short%20of%20its%20stated%20goal%20of%20decolonisation.%20We%20argue%20that%20the%20BNS%20expands%20powers%20of%20the%20state%20and%20the%20police%2C%20retains%20offences%20grounded%20in%20archaic%20morality%2C%20and%20widens%20the%20punitive%20network%20through%20broad%20and%20vaguely%20defined%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOffences%20against%20the%20state%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20markers%20of%20colonialism%20is%20a%20perpetual%20and%20continued%20expansion%20of%20the%20police%20powers%20that%20the%20State%20exerts%20over%20its%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcore.ac.uk%2Fdownload%2Fpdf%2F235410229.pdf%5C%22%3Esubjects%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcore.ac.uk%2Fdownload%2Fpdf%2F235410229.pdf%5C%22%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0The%20new%20criminal%20laws%20do%20little%20to%20steer%20away%20from%20the%20colonial%20mentality%20of%20an%20all-powerful%20state.%20Rather%2C%20by%20expanding%20police%20powers%20and%20creating%20provisions%20for%20vaguely%20defined%20but%20stringently%20punished%20offences%2C%20they%20deepen%20the%20power%20dynamic%20between%20state%20and%20citizen.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20perhaps%20the%20most%20significant%20vestige%20of%20coloniality%20in%20our%20criminal%20laws%20is%20the%20IPC%E2%80%99s%20chapter%2C%20%E2%80%98Offences%20Against%20the%20State%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20offence%20of%20sedition%20under%20Section%20124A.%20While%20the%20chapter%20remains%20largely%20unchanged%20in%20the%20BNS%2C%20%E2%80%98sedition%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20replaced%20by%20a%20new%20offence%2C%20defined%20in%20section%20152%20of%20the%20BNS%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Act%20endangering%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20and%20differs%20in%20some%20ways%20from%20its%20counterpart%20in%20the%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%20focuses%20on%20activities%20that%20excite%20hatred%2C%20contempt%20or%20disaffection%20towards%20the%20government%2C%20whereas%20Section%20152%20of%20the%20BNS%20penalises%20activities%20that%20excite%20%E2%80%98subversive%20activities%E2%80%99%20or%20encourage%20%E2%80%98feelings%20of%20separatist%20activities%E2%80%99%20or%20endanger%20the%20%E2%80%98sovereignty%20or%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India.%E2%80%99%20While%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98sedition%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20removed%20from%20the%20penal%20statute%2C%20the%20new%20provision%20appears%20to%20be%20as%20rights-restrictive%20as%20its%20counterpart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20BNS%20does%20not%20explain%20what%20constitutes%20exciting%20%E2%80%98subversive%20activities%E2%80%99%20or%20encouraging%20%E2%80%98feelings%20of%20separatist%20activities%E2%80%99.%20Post-independence%2C%20courts%20have%20had%20multiple%20occasions%20to%20interpret%20Section%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20Constitution.%20These%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F111867%2F%5C%22%3Edecisions%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%20had%20the%20effect%20of%20limiting%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20section%20to%20only%20curb%20speech%20that%20poses%20an%20imminent%20threat%20to%20public%20order.%20In%20this%20light%2C%20the%20scope%20of%20Section%20152%20of%20the%20BNS%E2%80%94a%20completely%20new%20provision%20with%20changed%20standards%E2%80%94is%20unclear%20since%20the%20tests%20evolved%20by%20the%20courts%20in%20decisions%20regarding%20Section%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%20no%20longer%20apply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Second%20Avatar%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%3A%20The%20Key%20Changes%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsecond-avatar-criminal-law-bills-has-anything-changed%5C%22%3ESecond%20Avatar%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%3A%20The%20Key%20Changes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsedition-to-go-but-endangering-unity-and-integrity-of-india-could-result-in-life-term%2Farticleshow%2F102661307.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ereasoned%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20new%20provision%20no%20longer%20criminalises%20%E2%80%98sedition%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3Erajdroh%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20but%20criminalises%20%E2%80%98treason%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3Edeshdroh%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20since%20criticising%20the%20government%20is%20no%20longer%20an%20offence.%20However%2C%20this%20does%20not%20signify%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20IPC.%20The%20Explanation%20to%20Section%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%20in%20any%20case%20exempts%20from%20its%20ambit%20any%20comments%20criticising%20governmental%20measures%20that%20do%20not%20excite%20feelings%20of%20hatred%20and%20disaffection%20as%20defined%20in%20the%20provision.%20Section%20152%20of%20the%20BNS%20lays%20down%20a%20similar%20exception.%20Thus%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20how%20the%20standards%20under%20the%20new%20provision%20are%20substantially%20different%20from%20those%20under%20the%20older%20provision.%C2%A0Moreover%2C%20the%20concern%20about%20sedition%20law%20has%20always%20been%20about%20how%20the%20state%20has%20utilised%20it%20to%20stifle%20dissent%20through%20arrest%20and%20extended%20detention%20of%20persons.%20Most%20cases%20do%20not%20lead%20to%20conviction%20(as%20reflected%20in%20the%20NCRB%20Data%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fnationalcrimerecordsbureau%2Fcustom%2F1702032406TABLE10A7.pdf%5C%22%3E2022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fnationalcrimerecordsbureau%2Fpost%2F1679664222TABLE10A7.pdf%5C%22%3E2021%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2F2022%2FJuly%2F11%2Fcustom%2Fcrime-in-india%2Ftable-10A.7-2020.pdf%5C%22%3E2020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2F2022%2FJuly%2F11%2Fcustom%2Fcrime-in-india%2Ftable-10A.7_1-2019.pdf%5C%22%3E2019%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2F2022%2FJuly%2F11%2Fcustom%2Fcrime-in-india%2Ftable-10A.7-2018.pdf%5C%22%3E2018%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20and%20the%20criminal%20process%20itself%20becomes%20the%20punishment.%20This%20has%20been%20facilitated%20by%20broadly%20worded%20provisions%20that%20empower%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20to%20detain%20individuals.%20Creating%20more%20ambiguity%20in%20the%20standards%20for%20these%20offences%20will%20only%20increase%20their%20harmful%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemnants%20of%20archaic%20moralism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20important%20sign%20of%20the%20colonial%20legacy%20of%20the%20IPC%20is%20the%20Victorian%20morality%20encoded%20in%20it.%20This%20is%20exemplified%20in%20the%20marital%20rape%20exception%20(Section%20375%2C%20IPC)%20and%20in%20language%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98outraging%20the%20modesty%20of%20a%20woman%E2%80%99%20(Section%20354%2C%20IPC)%2C%20the%20understanding%20of%20obscenity%20(defined%20in%20Section%20292%2C%20IPC)%2C%20and%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20abortion%20(Section%20312%2C%20IPC).%20We%20discuss%20each%20of%20these%20in%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EException%20to%20marital%20rape%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20marital%20rape%20exception%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Frape-is-rape-no-exceptions%2F%5C%22%3Erooted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20notion%20of%20irrevocable%20consent%20upon%20marriage.%20This%20was%20first%20articulated%20by%20Matthew%20Hale%2C%20who%20wrote%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20for%20a%20husband%20to%20be%20guilty%20of%20rape%20upon%20his%20wife%2C%20since%20marriage%20implies%20irrevocable%20consent%20to%20sexual%20intercourse%20on%20her%20part.%20This%20principle%20was%20entrenched%20in%20English%20common%20law%2C%20and%20from%20there%2C%20found%20its%20way%20into%20the%20IPC.%20While%20the%20UK%20House%20of%20Lords%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bailii.org%2Fuk%2Fcases%2FUKHL%2F1991%2F12.html%5C%22%3Estruck%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20exception%20in%201991%2C%20it%20continued%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20IPC.%20The%20Justice%20Verma%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20(2013)%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FJustice_Verma_Amendmenttocriminallaw_Jan2013.pdf%5C%22%3Erecommendation%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20remove%20this%20exception%20was%20not%C2%A0%20implemented%20in%20the%20subsequent%20amendment%20of%20the%20IPC.%20Recently%2C%20a%20Division%20Bench%20of%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20delivered%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fras11052022cw2842015190346-417219.pdf%5C%22%3Esplit%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20a%20petition%20challenging%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20provision%2C%20and%20the%20issue%20is%20currently%20pending%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Given%20that%20this%20is%20an%20effort%20to%20rid%20our%20criminal%20justice%20system%20of%20colonial%20era%20laws%2C%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20BNS%20would%20have%20been%20the%20perfect%20opportunity%20to%20end%20the%20exception%2C%20and%20recognise%20the%20bodily%20integrity%20and%20sexual%20autonomy%20of%20married%20women.%20However%2C%20the%20BNS%2C%20in%20Section%2063%20(offence%20of%20rape)%20retains%20the%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOutraging%20the%20modesty%20of%20women%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20notable%20colonial%20inheritance%20in%20the%20IPC%20is%20the%20use%20of%20the%20language%20of%20%E2%80%98modesty%E2%80%99%20in%20Sections%20354%20and%20509%2C%20which%20stem%20from%20a%20patriarchal%20understanding%20of%20sexual%20violence.%20As%20one%20of%20us%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1jZhgimstCgGReUpBANLPu68wbUE7nbqe%2Fview%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0elsewhere%2C%20the%20centring%20of%20%E2%80%98modesty%E2%80%99%20in%20Section%20354%20of%20the%20IPC%20invariably%20moves%20the%20discussion%20to%20what%20constitutes%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20modesty%2C%20and%20whether%20the%20woman%20was%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98modest%20character%E2%80%99%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20so%20as%20to%20be%20able%20to%20claim%20that%20her%20modesty%20was%20outraged.%20This%20deviates%20from%20the%20understanding%20of%20sexual%20assault%20as%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20bodily%20autonomy%20of%20the%20victim%2C%20and%20thus%20allows%20notions%20of%20morality%20to%20inform%20decision%20making%20in%20cases%20of%20sexual%20violence.%20Recognising%20this%2C%20the%20Justice%20Verma%20Committee%20had%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FJustice_Verma_Amendmenttocriminallaw_Jan2013.pdf%5C%22%3Erecommended%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20redrafting%20and%20rewording%20of%20Section%20354.%20It%20suggested%20that%20references%20to%20%E2%80%98outraging%20the%20modesty%20of%20women%E2%80%99%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20provision%2C%20and%20be%20replaced%20with%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98sexual%20assault%E2%80%99.%20This%20change%20was%20not%20made%20when%20the%20IPC%20was%20amended%20in%202013.%20Implementing%20it%20in%20the%20new%20Code%20would%20have%20represented%20a%20substantive%20departure%20from%20language%20invoking%20colonial%20morality%2C%20based%20on%20notions%20of%20honour%2C%20chastity%2C%20and%20modesty%20in%20our%20laws.%20However%2C%20Sections%2074%20and%2079%20of%20the%20BNS%20retain%20the%20language%20of%20%E2%80%98modesty%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EObscenity%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20regarding%20obscenity%20in%20the%20IPC%20represent%20yet%20another%20instance%20of%20the%20moral%20conservatism%20of%20colonial%20era%20laws.%20Section%20292%20of%20the%20IPC%20penalises%20the%20sale%2C%20exhibition%2C%20publication%2C%20etc.%2C%20of%20any%20obscene%20material%2C%20and%20Section%20294%20penalises%20obscene%20actions%20in%20public.%20The%20test%20for%20determining%20what%20constitutes%20%E2%80%98obscenity%E2%80%99%20under%20these%20sections%20is%20if%20the%20materials%2Factions%20in%20question%20are%20%E2%80%98lascivious%E2%80%99%20or%20appeal%20to%20%E2%80%98prurient%20interests%E2%80%99%20or%20if%20they%20tend%20to%20%E2%80%98deprave%20and%20corrupt%E2%80%99%20people.%20In%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikisource.org%2Fwiki%2FRegina_v._Hicklin%5C%22%3ER%20v.%20Hicklin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20UK%20House%20of%20Lords%20held%20that%20all%20materials%20which%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20%E2%80%98deprave%20and%20corrupt%20those%20whose%20minds%20are%20open%20to%20such%20immoral%20influences%E2%80%99%20are%20obscene.%20This%20test%20was%20imported%20into%20Indian%20law%20through%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%201965%20decision%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1623275%2F%5C%22%3EUdeshi%20v.%20Maharashtra%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Court%20ruled%20that%20any%20material%20that%20involved%20%E2%80%98treating%20with%20(sic)%20sex%20in%20a%20manner%20appealing%20to%20the%20carnal%20side%20of%20human%20nature%2C%20or%20having%20that%20tendency%E2%80%99%20would%20be%20considered%20obscene.%20This%20implied%20that%20any%20material%20that%20tended%20to%20arouse%20sexual%20feelings%20would%20be%20deemed%20obscene%20within%20the%20meaning%20of%20the%20provision.%20In%202014%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F195958005%2F%5C%22%3ESarkar%20v.%20West%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0espoused%20a%20slightly%20modified%20test%20for%20obscenity%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98community%20standards%20test%2C%E2%80%99%20stating%20that%20%E2%80%98those%20sex-related%20materials%20which%20have%20a%20tendency%20of%20%E2%80%98exciting%20lustful%20thoughts%E2%80%99%20can%20be%20held%20to%20be%20obscene%E2%80%99%20with%20the%20caveat%20that%20%E2%80%98the%20obscenity%20has%20to%20be%20judged%20from%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20an%20average%20person%2C%20by%20applying%20contemporary%20community%20standards.%E2%80%99%20Both%20these%20tests%20for%20obscenity%20follow%20from%20the%20overbroad%20and%20subjective%20phrasing%20in%20the%20section%20itself%2C%20and%20depend%20entirely%20on%20personal%20and%20community%20morality%20to%20determine%20whether%20or%20not%20something%20is%20obscene.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ruled%20that%20it%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F168671544%2F%5C%22%3Econstitutional%20morality%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20not%20personal%20morality%2C%20that%20should%20inform%20criminalisation.%20This%20is%20the%20only%20way%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20standard%20of%20criminalisation%20is%20not%20solely%20based%20on%20whether%20the%20conduct%20in%20question%20offends%20one%E2%80%99s%20personal%20morality.%20Amending%20these%20provisions%20would%20have%20been%20a%20welcome%20step%20towards%20decolonising%20the%20law.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20BNS%20has%20retained%20the%20exact%20wording%20of%20the%20IPC%20provisions%20on%20obscenity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECriminalisation%20of%20abortion%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20remnant%20of%20moralism%20in%20our%20criminal%20laws%20is%20Section%20312%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20which%20criminalises%20abortion.%20Under%20this%20provision%20any%20person%20who%20voluntarily%20causes%20a%20woman%20to%20miscarry%20is%20liable%20to%20be%20punished.%20This%20also%20includes%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20who%20chooses%20abortion.%20The%20only%20exception%20is%20if%20such%20miscarriage%20is%20caused%20in%20good%20faith%20to%20save%20the%20pregnant%20woman%E2%80%99s%20life.%20The%20Medical%20Termination%20of%20Pregnancy%20Act%2C%201971%20(%E2%80%98MTP%20Act%E2%80%99)%20introduces%20further%20exceptions%20to%20this%20provision%20by%20protecting%20doctors%20from%20criminal%20liability%2C%20if%20they%20perform%20abortions%20under%20specific%20conditions%20prescribed%20under%20the%20Act.%20While%20the%20MTP%20Act%20has%20liberalised%20access%20to%20abortions%2C%20it%20relies%20on%20creating%20exceptions%20to%20the%20norm%20of%20criminalising%20abortion%20procedures.%20The%20introduction%20of%20a%20rights-based%20framework%20on%20abortion%E2%80%94another%20missed%20opportunity%E2%80%94would%20have%20constituted%20a%20substantive%20step%20towards%20decolonisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20not%20using%20this%20opportunity%20to%20alter%20the%20law%20on%20these%20issues%2C%20the%20new%20Codes%20have%20actually%20reinforced%20and%20legitimised%20the%20pre-existing%20coloniality%20in%20our%20criminal%20statutes.%20Besides%20the%20specific%20provisions%20mapped%20above%2C%20the%20strongest%20counter%20to%20the%20logic%20of%20decolonisation%20is%20arguably%20the%20lack%20of%20any%20meaningful%20reform%20in%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20laws.%20The%20colonial%20logic%20of%20the%20law%2C%20in%20large%20part%2C%20lay%20in%20its%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Flaw-and-history-review%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fcodification-and-the-rule-of-colonial-difference-criminal-procedure-in-british-india%2F6163423C0490CAE1B323CB97CC89E2F5%5C%22%3Edifferentiated%20application%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0across%20white%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98native%E2%80%99%20populations.%20Even%20among%20the%20%E2%80%98natives%E2%80%99%2C%20class%2C%20caste%20and%20social%20stature%20determined%20outcomes%20in%20criminal%20cases.%20This%20colonial%20mentality%20continues%20till%20today%2C%20as%20is%20evident%20from%20prison%20statistics%20revealing%20that%20the%20criminal%20legal%20apparatus%20has%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fnationalcrimerecordsbureau%2Fcustom%2Fpsiyearwise2022%2F1701613297PSI2022ason01122023.pdf%5C%22%3Edisparate%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20oppressed%20castes%20and%20religious%20minorities.%20While%20the%20new%20criminal%20laws%20claim%20to%20place%20the%20citizen%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20justice%20delivery%20process%2C%20there%20is%20absolutely%20no%20mention%20of%20undoing%20the%20discriminatory%20impact%20and%20enforcement%20of%20the%20laws.%20In%20fact%2C%20by%20strengthening%20the%20state%20in%20an%20increasingly%20unequal%20society%2C%20these%20gaps%20will%20only%20be%20widened.%20Moreover%2C%20given%20the%20reality%20of%20large%20portions%20of%20BNS%2C%20BNSS%20and%20BSA%20being%20reproduced%20verbatim%20from%20the%20IPC%2C%20CrPC%2C%20and%20the%20IEA%2C%20the%20opportunity%20for%20a%20meaningful%20overhaul%20of%20the%20injustices%20perpetrated%20by%20the%20criminal%20legal%20system%20has%20been%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nls.ac.in%2Ffaculty%2Fmrinal-satish%2F%5C%22%3EMrinal%20Satish%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Law%20at%20NLSIU%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nls.ac.in%2Ffaculty%2Fpreeti-pratishruti-dash%2F%5C%22%3EPreeti%20Pratishruti%20Dash%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Law%20at%20NLSIU%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nls.ac.in%2Fpeople%2Fanushka-pandey%2F%5C%22%3EAnushka%20Pandey%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Research%20Associate%20at%20NLSIU.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nls.ac.in%2Fblog%2Fbharatiya-nyaya-sanhita-decolonising-or-reinforcing-colonial-ideas%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%20blog.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706617825000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11180259%2FUneven.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbharatiya-nyay-sanhita-decolonising-or-reinforcing-colonial-ideas%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20Codes%20have%20actually%20reinforced%20and%20legitimised%20the%20pre-existing%20coloniality%20in%20our%20criminal%20statutes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbharatiya-nyay-sanhita-decolonising-or-reinforcing-colonial-ideas%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Revealed%3A%20Hrithik's%20unique%20pre-shoot%20ritual%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706617753000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107265489%2Cimgsize-23000.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainmen