%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deals%20came%20as%20NATO%20is%20racing%20to%20fill%20up%20its%20stockpiles%20with%20cutting-edge%20weaponry%20in%20preparation%20for%20a%20showdown%20with%20Moscow%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Ffiscal-year-2023-u-s-arms-transfers-and-defense-trade%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efact%20sheet%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20citing%20the%20numbers%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20State%20specified%20that%20arms%20exports%20rose%20to%20%2480.9%20billion%20in%202023%2C%20a%2055.9%25%20increase%20from%20%2451.9%20billion%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20represented%20the%20US'%20%26quot%3Bhighest%20annual%20total%20of%20sales%20and%20assistance%20provided%20to%20our%20allies%20and%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sum%2C%20plus%20the%20%24157.5%20billion%20sold%20in%20military%20equipment%20through%20private%20US%20companies%20to%20foreign%20governments%20in%202023%2C%20adds%20up%20to%20%24238.5%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20an%20all-time%20record%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Faerospace-defense%2Fus-arms-exports-hit-record-high-fiscal-2023-2024-01-29%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccording%20to%20Reuters%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArms%20transfers%20and%20defense%20trade%20are%20%26quot%3Bimportant%20US%20foreign%20policy%20tools%20with%20potential%20long-term%20implications%20for%20regional%20and%20global%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20State%20Department%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMira%20Resnick%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20State%20Department's%20Office%20of%20Regional%20Security%20and%20Arms%20Transfers%2C%20went%20further%2C%20telling%20Politico%20that%20this%20surge%20in%20sales%20is%20evidence%20that%20Russia's%20defense%20industry%20is%20%26quot%3Bfailing%20and%20continues%20to%20fail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20that%20because%20Russia's%20defense%20industry%20is%20denied%20the%20resources%20that%20come%20from%20exports%2C%20that%20helps%20to%20contribute%20to%20Russian%20strategic%20failure%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResnick%20cited%20a%20%241.8%20billion%20arms%20deal%20that%20the%20US%20struck%20with%20India%20last%20year%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Breal%20tough%20decisions%26quot%3B%20in%20Global%20South%20countries%20about%20abandoning%20Russian%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sipri.org%2Fmedia%2Fpress-release%2F2023%2Fsurge-arms-imports-europe-while-us-dominance-global-arms-trade-increases%23%3A~%3Atext%3DRussia%2527s%2520arms%2520exports%2520fell%2520by%2C%25E2%2580%259317%2520and%25202018%25E2%2580%259322.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edata%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Stockholm%20International%20Peace%20Research%20Institute%2C%20Russia's%20share%20of%20global%20arms%20exports%20was%20already%20falling%20before%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20from%2022%25%20between%202013%20and%202017%2C%20to%2016%25%20between%202018%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20Russian%20arms%20exports%20have%20declined%20in%20part%20due%20to%20China%20and%20India's%20efforts%20to%20ramp%20up%20their%20own%20domestic%20arms%20production%2C%20along%20with%20earlier%20Western%20sanctions%20packages%20meant%20to%20dissuade%20third%20countries%20from%20buying%20Russian%20weapons.%20This%20is%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fsellers-remorse-challenges-facing-russias-arms-exports%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Russian%2520arms%2520export%2520industry%2Cstrengthen%2520their%2520domestic%2520arms%2520production.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20or%20CSIS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20subsequent%20Western%20sanctions%20have%20exacerbated%20that%20downward%20trend%20by%20putting%20a%20burden%20on%20Russia's%20defense%20production%20capacity%2C%20damaging%20Russian%20arms'%20reputation%2C%20and%20making%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20the%20Kremlin's%20clients%20to%20make%20payments%2C%20the%20CSIS%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202023%2C%20the%20Indian%20military%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findia-says-russia-not-delivering-weapons-everything-to-ukraine-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Russia%20failed%20to%20supply%20weapons%20it%20had%20been%20contracted%20to%20deliver%20because%20it%20was%20embroiled%20in%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-arms-exports-rise-50-percent-cutting-russia-weapons-trade-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706617627000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b8d631ac2de4f17ee5b201%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-arms-exports-rise-50-percent-cutting-russia-weapons-trade-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20helped%20increase%20US%20arms%20exports%20to%20%2481%20billion%20in%202023%2C%20Politico%20reported%2C%20while%20also%20damaging%20Russia's%20weapons%20trade.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tspirlet%40insider.com%20(Thibault%20Spirlet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-arms-exports-rise-50-percent-cutting-russia-weapons-trade-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Red%20Sea%20crisis%3A%20India%20on%20track%20to%20export%20record-low%20diesel%20to%20Europe%20in%20Jan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706617614000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Fart