the%20firm%20informed%20the%20FT.%20The%20firm's%20hybrid%20working%20policy%20requires%20staff%20to%20come%20into%20the%20office%20twice%20a%20week%2C%20but%20at%20least%2050%25%20of%20some%20teams%20are%20flouting%20this%20rule.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20person%20told%20the%20FT%20that%20some%20partners%20are%20being%20shown%20data%20that%20connects%20office%20attendance%20to%20mid-year%20performance%20ratings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20source%20said%20the%20statistics%20would%20be%20used%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcarrot%20rather%20than%20a%20stick%26quot%3B%20strategy%20to%20encourage%20teams%20to%20follow%20its%20hybrid%20working%20policies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEY%20is%20the%20latest%20in%20a%20string%20of%20financial%20services%20and%20consultancy%20companies%20firms%20to%20put%20strict%20return-to-office%20mandates%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcitigroup-monitoring-office-attendance-absent-staff-fired-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECitigroup%20started%20monitoring%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20workers%20were%20coming%20in%20for%20the%20required%20three%20days%20a%20week%20by%20checking%20swipe%20card%20data%20in%20August.%20It%20said%20workers%20who%20are%20consistently%20not%20in%20the%20office%20may%20be%20disciplined%20from%20adjusted%20bonuses%20to%20being%20fired.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20JPMorgan%20required%20employees%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-jpmorgan-tracks-employees-zoom-calls-id-swipes-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereturn%20to%20its%20office%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20three%20to%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20depending%20on%20seniority.%20It%20also%20collected%20data%20to%20see%20which%20employees%20were%20meeting%20its%20in-office%20quotas%20and%20compiled%20it%20into%20reports%20for%20managers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Kevin%20Ellis%2C%20the%20boss%20of%20another%20Big%20Four%20firm%20PWC%2C%20recently%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-01-15%2Fai-means-young-staff-should-work-in-the-office-says-pwc-uk-boss-kevin-ellis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ejunior%20workers%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eneed%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20more%20to%20progress%20because%20AI%20is%20ready%20to%20take%20over%20parts%20of%20their%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20asking%20me%20my%20opinion%20on%20how%20you%20succeed%20in%20your%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum.%20%26quot%3BI'd%20be%20in%20the%20office%20four%20to%20five%20days%20a%20week.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEY%20declined%20to%20comment%20when%20contacted%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fey-tracking-office-attendance-data-teams-disregard-rto-policies-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706616527000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b8c9b87a3d27148875abb9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fey-tracking-office-attendance-data-teams-disregard-rto-policies-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Senior%20employees%20at%20EY%20are%20looking%20at%20%26quot%3Bturnstile%20access%26quot%3B%20and%20swipe%20card%20entry%20data%20to%20check%20if%20staff%20are%20complying%20with%20return-to-office%20rules.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbhaimiya%40insider.com%20(Sawdah%20Bhaimiya)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fey-tracking-office-attendance-data-teams-disregard-rto-policies-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22TCS%20bags%2015-year%20deal%20from%20UK-headquartered%20insurance%20company%20Aviva%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706616183000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-03%2F19%2Ffull%2F1616154354-133.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftcs-extends-contract-with-aviva-for-15-year-124013000643_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22TCS's%20scope%20of%20work%20will%20expand%20to%20cover%20over%205.5%20million%20policies%2C%20to%20be%20managed%20by%20Diligenta%2C%20TCS's%20Financial%20Conduct%20Authority%20(FCA)%20regulated%20subsidiary%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20Aviva%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftcs-extends-contract-with-aviva-for-15-year-124013000643_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftcs-extends-contract-with-aviva-for-15-year-124013000643_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftcs-extends-contract-with-aviva-for-15-year-124013000643_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Does%20'Integral%20Humanism'%20Really%20Mean%20to%20the%20BJP%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30161148%2F406110211_773446158163006_4756603232278021214_n.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20third%20page%20of%20its%20constitution%2C%20the%20BJP%20lays%20out%20its%20membership%20conditions%3A%20%E2%80%9CAny%20Indian%20citizen%20of%2018%20years%20or%20above%20who%20accepts%20Articles%20II%2C%20III%20and%20IV%20of%20the%20constitution%20shall%2C%20on%20making%20a%20written%20declaration%E2%80%A6%20become%20a%20member%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20BJP.%20What%20are%20these%20things%20that%20are%20important%20enough%20to%20make%20a%20written%20declaration%3F%20Article%20II%20of%20the%20BJP%20constitution%20concludes%20thus%3A%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20party%20shall%20bear%20true%20faith%20and%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20as%20by%20law%20established%20and%20to%20the%20principles%20of%20socialism%2C%20secularism%20and%20democracy%E2%80%9D.%20Article%20IV%20says%20the%20party%20commits%20itself%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9CGandhian%20approach%20to%20socio-economic%20issues%20leading%20to%20establishment%20of%20egalitarian%20society%20free%20from%20exploitation%E2%80%9D.%20It%20adds%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cparty%20stands%20for%20decentralisation%20of%20economic%20and%20political%20power%E2%80%9D.%3Cb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhere%20do%20these%20matters%20figure%20in%20the%20way%20the%20party%20actually%20conducts%20itself%3F%20This%20will%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20for%20another%20time.%20Article%20III%2C%20the%20subject%20of%20this%20column%2C%20is%20a%20single%20line%20which%20reads%20%E2%80%9CIntegral%20Humanism%20shall%20be%20the%20basic%20philosophy%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%9D.%20Integral%20Humanism%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20four%20lectures%20in%20Mumbai%20given%20by%20Deen%20Dayal%20Upadhyaya%20between%20April%2022%20and%2025%2C%201965.%20Upadhyaya%20held%20a%20BA%20degree%20and%20was%20a%20journalist%20at%20the%20RSS%E2%80%99s%20in-house%20Panchjanya.%20He%20was%20about%2050%20when%20he%20delivered%20these%20lectures%20and%20became%20president%20of%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20(the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20precursor)%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20after%20he%20delivered%20them.%20The%20following%20is%20a%20summary%20of%20the%20argument%20Upadhyaya%20presents%3A%3Cb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*The%20cause%20of%20the%20problems%20facing%20Bharat%20is%20a%20neglect%20of%20national%20identity.%20The%20nation%20is%20like%20an%20individual%20and%20becomes%20ill%20if%20its%20natural%20instincts%20are%20disregarded%20or%20suppressed.%20Seventeen%20years%20after%20Independence%2C%20India%20was%20undecided%20about%20the%20direction%20it%20would%20take%20towards%20development.%20Independence%20is%20meaningful%20only%20it%20is%20the%20instrument%20to%20express%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*The%20focus%20in%20India%20was%20on%20episodic%20problems%3A%20economic%2C%20social%20and%20political.%20This%20was%20because%20India%20adopted%20a%20Western%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20economic%2C%20social%20and%20political%20doctrines%20along%20with%20Western%20science.%20Westernisation%20was%20synonymous%20with%20progress%20for%20Indians.%20However%2C%20the%20West%20was%20unable%20to%20reconcile%20nationalism%2C%20democracy%20and%20socialism.%20These%20were%20essentially%20Western%20ideals%20and%20they%20were%20all%20in%20conflict%20with%20one%20another.%20These%20ideologies%20were%20not%20universal%20and%20not%20free%20from%20the%20limitations%20of%20the%20people%20and%20cultures%20which%20gave%20birth%20to%20these%20isms.%20Ayurveda%20said%20that%20we%20need%20to%20find%20local%20cures%20to%20local%20diseases.%20Could%20Bharatiya%20culture%20provide%20a%20solution%20for%20the%20world%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Dharma%20is%20given%20foremost%20place%20in%20Bharatiya%20culture.%20Dharma%20is%20the%20natural%20law%20that%20is%20eternal%20and%20universally%20applicable.%20Dharma%20is%20ethics%20teaching%20us%20not%20to%20lie%2C%20not%20to%20fight.%20When%20nature%20is%20directed%20according%20to%20the%20principles%20of%20dharma%2C%20there%20is%20culture%20and%20civilisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Dharma%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20executive%2C%20legislative%20and%20judiciary.%20It%20is%20also%20higher%20than%20the%20people.%20If%20out%20of%20450%20million%20Indians%2C%20all%20except%20one%20voted%20for%20something%2C%20it%20would%20still%20be%20wrong%20if%20it%20was%20against%20dharma.%20The%20people%20have%20no%20right%20to%20act%20against%20dharma.%20The%20words%20%E2%80%9Csecularism%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdharmnirpeksh%E2%80%9D%20(the%20Hindi%20phrase%20for%20secularism%20meaning%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20which%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20dharma%E2%80%9D)%20in%20the%20Constitution%20are%20wrong%20and%20bad%20because%20dharma%20is%20a%20necessary%20condition%20for%20the%20State.%20That%20which%20is%20not%20based%20on%20dharma%20is%20unacceptable%2C%20and%20therefore%20secularism%20was%20fatally%20flawed.%20National%20unity%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20dharma%3B%20so%20diversity%20was%20problematic.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20needs%20to%20be%20changed%20from%20federal%20to%20unitary%2C%20with%20no%20legislative%20powers%20for%20the%20states%2C%20only%20for%20the%20Centre.%20Conflict%20between%20individuals%20and%20institutions%20of%20society%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20decadence%20and%20perversion.%20The%20West%20was%20wrong%20to%20see%20the%20adversarial%20relationship%20between%20the%20individual%20and%20the%20State%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20progress.%20The%20individual%20was%20made%20up%20of%20body%2C%20mind%2C%20intelligence%20and%20soul.%20A%20human%20being%20is%20born%20with%20a%20soul.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPersonality%2C%20soul%20and%20character%20are%20different%20from%20one%20another.%20The%20person%E2%80%99s%20soul%20is%20unaffected%20by%20personal%20history.%20Similarly%2C%20national%20culture%20is%20continuously%20modified%20by%20history.%20Culture%20includes%20all%20things%20held%20as%20good%20and%20commendable%2C%20but%20they%20do%20not%20affect%20%E2%80%9Cchiti%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20national%20soul.%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20soul%20is%20fundamental%20and%20central.%20Chiti%20determines%20the%20direction%20of%20cultural%20advance.%20It%20filters%20out%20what%20is%20to%20be%20excluded%20from%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Societies%20are%20animate%20and%20a%20society%20has%20a%20body%2C%20mind%2C%20intellect%20and%20soul.%20Some%20Westerners%20were%20beginning%20to%20accept%20this%20truth.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20William%20McDougall%2C%20said%20that%20a%20group%20had%20a%20mind%20and%20a%20psychology%2C%20its%20own%20methods%20of%20thinking%20and%20action%20just%20as%20an%20individual%20did.%20Societies%20have%20an%20inborn%20nature%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20based%20on%20its%20history.%20Events%20don%E2%80%99t%20affect%20it.%20This%20group%20nature%20is%20like%20the%20soul%20in%20individuals%2C%20also%20unaffected%20by%20history.%20This%20group%20mentality%20is%20like%20mob%20mentality%20but%20developed%20over%20a%20longer%20period.%20The%20nation%20needs%20both%20an%20ideal%20and%20a%20motherland%20and%20only%20then%20is%20it%20a%20nation.%20The%20State%20exists%20to%20protect%20this%20nation%2C%20which%20has%20an%20ideal%20and%20a%20motherland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20message%20of%20the%20four%20lectures.%20It%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20the%20meaning%20of%20it%20all%20is.%20What%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20the%20difference%20between%20mind%20and%20intelligence%3F%20What%20is%20a%20soul%3F%20How%20are%20these%20three%20things%20separate%20from%20a%20body%3F%20What%20does%20the%20sentence%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpersonality%2C%20soul%20and%20character%20are%20all%20distinct%20from%20one%20another%E2%80%9D%20really%20mean%3F%20And%20what%20is%20the%20role%20of%20a%20political%20party%20and%20of%20government%20in%20any%20of%20this%3F%20The%20national%20soul%2C%20%E2%80%9Cchiti%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20group%20mind%20are%20not%20scientific%20phenomena%20and%20the%20works%20of%20William%20McDougall%20are%20not%20science%20(he%20thought%2C%20like%20Upadhyaya%20did%2C%20that%20the%20mind%20influenced%20evolution).%20One%20wonders%20how%20many%20BJP%20members%20who%20sign%20written%20declarations%20saying%20they%20accept%20Integral%20Humanism%20as%20their%20%E2%80%9Cbasic%20philosophy%E2%80%9D%20actually%20understand%20what%20it%20is%20that%20they%20have%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAakar%20Patel%20is%20an%20author%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706616039000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30161148%2F406110211_77344615816