azy%20rhetoric%2C%20followed%20the%20more%20traditional%20divide-and-rule%20strategy%20by%20cosying%20up%20to%20Russia%20while%20applying%20extreme%20pressure%20on%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHalford%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20geopolitics%20lives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20has%20merely%20served%20to%20further%20cement%20Sino-Russian%20cooperation%2C%20and%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20reinvigorating%20the%20Eurasian%20dream%20by%20exploiting%20the%20latest%20developments%20in%20railroad%20technology.%20They%20are%20now%20practically%20realising%20British%20geopolitical%20theorist%20Halford%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20prediction%2C%20in%201904%2C%20that%20the%20inner%20area%20of%20Eurasia%2C%20impenetrable%20by%20sea%20power%2C%20would%20become%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FThe_Geographical_Pivot_of_History%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CPivot%20Area%E2%80%9D%20of%20world%20politics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20prediction%20about%20the%20relative%20decline%20of%20maritime%20power%20due%20to%20the%20superiority%20of%20rail%20over%20ships%20in%20terms%20of%20speed%20and%20penetration%20is%20no%20longer%20far-fetched.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELook%20at%20the%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalaffairs.org%2Fresearch%2Freport%2Feurasias-freight-infrastructure-vs-russias-war-ukraine%5C%22%3EOnly%2017%20freight%20trains%20%3C%2Fa%3Eran%20from%20China%20to%20Europe%20in%202011.%20Today%20more%20than%2060%2C000%20trains%20cumulatively%20ply%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass%20and%20its%20maritime%20margins.%20Current%20advances%20in%20rail%20technology%20and%20online%20trade%20trends%20that%20demand%20reduced%20delivery%20time%C2%A0%20are%20indicative%20of%20the%20growing%20salience%20of%20transcontinental%20rail%20connectivity%20in%20conduct%20of%20international%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEurasian%20landmass%20connectivity%20%E2%80%93%20railway%20corridor%20passing%20through%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20Belarus%20%E2%80%93%20impacts%20the%20overall%20economic%20effects%20of%20American%20naval%20capabilities%20to%20cut%20off%20Chinese%20trade%20and%20supply%20routes%20at%20Malacca%20straits.%C2%A0%20The%20Chinese%20answer%20to%20its%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgjia.georgetown.edu%2F2023%2F03%2F22%2Fchinas-economic-security-challenge-difficulties-overcoming-the-malacca-dilemma%2F%5C%22%3EMalacca%20Dilemma%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20naval%20blockade%20of%20vital%20Chinese%20sea%20lines%20of%20communication%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20the%20carving%20out%20of%20alternative%20trade%20routes%20to%20the%20West%2C%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Europe.%20However%2C%20the%20Chinese%20alternative%20trade%20routes%20are%20dependent%20on%20Russian%20cooperation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FCEFT%5C%22%3EThe%20China-Europe%20Freight%20Train%20(CEFT)%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20Russia%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cas%20both%20the%20most%20important%20terminus%20and%20through-corridor%20accounting%20for%2037%25%20of%20all%20CEFTs%20through%202021%2C%20leading%20Germany%20at%2024.3%25%20and%20Poland%20at%2023.4%25.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerica%20did%20not%20tolerate%20Sino-Soviet%20unity%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20and%20it%20will%20not%20do%20so%20now.%20The%20war%20in%20Europe%20has%20disrupted%20the%20development%20of%20these%20connectivity%20projects%20due%20to%20sanctions%20imposed%20on%20Russia%2C%20thereby%20adversely%20impacting%C2%A0China%E2%80%99s%20long-term%20interests%20in%20the%20Eurasian%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20many%20companies%20operating%20rail%20freight%20between%20China%20and%20the%20EU%20are%20avoiding%20transit%20through%20Russia%2C%20resulting%20in%20greater%20use%20of%20the%20Middle%20Corridor%20(the%20Trans-Caspian%20International%20Transport%20Route)%E2%80%94from%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20China%20through%20Kazakhstan%2C%20the%20Caspian%20Sea%2C%20Azerbaijan%2C%20and%20Georgia%E2%80%94as%20an%20alternative%20route%2C%20causing%20longer%20journeys%20and%20increased%20costs.%20The%20West%20is%20likely%20to%20support%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20fight%20against%20Russia%20until%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20latter%20is%20economically%20and%20militarily%20exhausted%20and%20willing%20to%20reassess%20its%20look-east%20policy%20and%C2%A0relationship%20with%20China.%20This%20looks%20a%20long%20way%20off%2C%20and%20promises%20continuation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cforever%20wars%E2%80%9D%20dispensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20the%20recent%20Pakistan-Iran%20conflict%2C%20what%20has%20come%20to%20light%20is%20the%20involvement%20of%20Balochistan%2C%20with%20the%20Gwadar%20port%20located%20close%20to%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Oman%2C%20an%20important%20link%20in%20the%20new%20silk%20road%20envisaged%20by%20China.%20Damascus%E2%80%94the%20traditional%20terminus%20node%20of%20the%20ancient%20Silk%20Road%E2%80%94is%20also%20embroiled%20in%20a%20conflict%20situation%20and%20is%20a%20pariah%20state%20in%20the%20western%20geopolitical%20equation.%20In%202022%2C%20there%20were%20clashes%20on%20the%20Tajikistan-Kyrgyzstan%20border.%20In%20the%20beginning%20of%202022%2C%20Kazakistan%20witnessed%20violent%20protests%20against%20President%20Kassym-Jomart%20Tokayev%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20The%20Armenia-Azerbaijan%20hostilities%20over%20the%20disputed%20Nagorno-Karabakh%20republic%20provide%20America%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20meddle%20in%20Central%20Asia%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20China-Russia%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20build%20the%20Berlin-Baghdad%20rail%20link%20became%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20reasons%20for%20World%20War%20I%2C%20as%20they%20threatened%20the%20British-controlled%20sea%20lanes%20of%20communication%20passing%20through%20the%20Suez%20Canal.%20It%20was%20seen%20as%20part%20of%20an%20inter-imperial%20assault%20on%20the%20British%20empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20the%20major%20colonial%20powers%20faced%20growing%20political%20discontent%2C%20economic%20inequality%2C%20mass%20immiseration%2C%20and%20the%20emergence%20of%20powerful%20trade%20union%2C%20worker%2C%20and%20socialist%20movements%20against%20capitalism%20and%20empire.%20A%20world%20war%20resulted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%2021%20century%2C%20we%20live%20in%20a%20world%20best%20described%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheroadsinitiative.org%2Fpoly-crisis-or-organic-crisis-the-crisis-of-the-united-states-and-the-us-led-world-order%2F%5C%22%3Ecrisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20called%20%E2%80%9Cpoly%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cperma%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20organic.%20At%20home%20in%20so%20many%20countries%20across%20the%20world%2C%20we%20see%20popular%20resistance%20to%20elite%20rule%2C%20crises%20of%20legitimacy%20and%20authority%2C%20increasing%20political%20polarisation%20and%20violence%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20right-wing%20racist%2C%20and%20communal%20divide%20and%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobally%2C%20the%20geopolitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20cracks%20in%20a%20system%20of%20complex%20interdependence%20are%20evolving%20into%20schisms.%20The%20struggle%20for%20hegemony%20and%20empire%20is%20increasingly%20breaking%20out%20into%20violence.%20The%20world%20appears%20to%20be%20heading%20towards%20another%20major%20war%20on%20a%20global%20scale%20over%20supply%20lines%2C%20alternative%20trade%20routes%2C%20control%20of%20the%20seas%2C%20and%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass.%20Flashpoints%20from%20Ukraine%20to%20Gaza%20to%20Yemen%20to%20Taiwan%20%E2%80%93%20disciplinary%20military%20confrontations%20for%20containment%20on%20the%20borders%20of%20Eurasia%20and%20its%20core%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Atul%20Bhardwaj%20is%20an%20honorary%20research%20fellow%20in%20the%20department%20of%20international%20politics%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EIndia-America%20Relations%20(1942-62)%3A%20Rooted%20in%20the%20Liberal%20International%20Order%20%3Cem%3E(Routledge%2C%202018)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fiparmar%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EInderjeet%20Parmar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20international%20politics%20and%20associate%20dean%20of%20research%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Policy%20and%20Global%20Affairs%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20a%20fellow%20of%20the%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20and%20a%20columnist%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20an%20International%20Fellow%20at%20the%20ROADS%20Initiative%20think%20tank%2C%20Islamabad%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20author%20of%20several%20books%20including%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EFoundations%20of%20the%20American%20Century%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20history%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20powers%20of%20the%20US%20Foreign%20Policy%20Establishment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706614216000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F20120344%2FAnti-terrorist_operation_in_eastern_Ukraine_War_Ukraine_26894689722.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fflashpoints-in-ukraine-gaza-yemen-and-taiwan-point-to-a-global-war-in-the-making%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Globally%2C%20the%20geopolitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20cracks%20in%20a%20system%20of%20complex%20interdependence%20are%20evolving%20into%20schisms.%20The%20world%20appears%20to%20be%20heading%20towards%20another%20major%20war%20on%20a%20global%20scale%20over%20supply%20lines%2C%20alternative%20trade%20routes%2C%20control%20of%20the%20seas%2C%20and%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fflashpoints-in-ukraine-gaza-ye