nemployment-rate-job-growth-labor-market-wages-december-economic-outlook-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EJob%20growth%20in%20December%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20far%20surpassed%20economists'%20forecasts%20%E2%80%94%20with%20growth%20of%20216%2C000%20compared%20to%20a%20forecast%20of%20170%2C000%20for%20that%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20continuing%20strength%20in%20the%20labor%20market%20does%20represent%20a%20slowdown%20from%20the%20hot%20post-pandemic%20recovery%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPayroll%20employment%20rose%20by%202.7%20million%20in%202023%20(an%20average%20monthly%20gain%20of%20225%2C000)%2C%20less%20than%20the%20increase%20of%204.8%20million%20in%202022%20(an%20average%20monthly%20gain%20of%20399%2C000)%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20news%20release%20in%20early%20January%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20still%20challenges%20ahead%20for%20the%20Fed%20as%20the%20economy%20settles%20into%20a%20new%20normal.%20Nick%20Bunker%2C%20economic%20research%20director%20for%20North%20America%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20early%20January%20that%20%26quot%3Bwage%20growth%20isn't%20slowing%20maybe%20as%20quickly%20as%20some%20people%20would've%20hoped.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20hourly%20earnings%20grew%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E4.1%25%20year%20over%20year%20in%20December%2C%20which%20isn't%20far%20off%20from%20the%20year-over-year%20changes%20seen%20in%20the%20months%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20economic%20strength%20could%20also%20mean%20the%20Fed%20waits%20longer%20before%20cutting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20nothing%20in%20the%20economy%20compelling%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates%20as%20soon%20as%20March%20%E2%80%94%20which%20investors%20have%20been%20pinning%20their%20hopes%20to%20%E2%80%94%20so%20expect%20the%20Fed%20to%20push%20back%20by%20emphasizing%20that%20inflation%20still%20needs%20to%20show%20further%20improvement%2C%26quot%3B%20Greg%20McBride%2C%20chief%20financial%20analyst%20for%20Bankrate%2C%20said%20ahead%20of%20the%20Fed%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-up-how-consumer-price-index-looked-december-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInflation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20measured%20by%20the%20consumer%20price%20index%2C%20or%20CPI%2C%20has%20been%20far%20below%20its%20decades-high%20peak%20in%20June%202022.%20The%20year-over-year%20percent%20change%20in%20CPI%20was%203.4%25%20in%20December%202023%2C%20surpassing%20the%203.1%25%20in%20November%20but%20not%20as%20high%20as%20earlier%20in%20the%20year%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%206.4%25%20rate%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20January%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20inflation%20in%20the%20country%20is%20still%20persistently%20elevated%2C%20David%20Kelly%2C%20chief%20global%20strategist%20at%20J.P.%20Morgan%20Asset%20Management%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fpulse%2Ftoo-much-growth-early-easing-david-kelly-ycqje%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enote%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Fed%20is%20unlikely%20to%20start%20cutting%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bottom%20line%20is%20that%2C%20while%20inflation%20continues%20to%20moderate%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Fed's%20hopes%2C%20economic%20growth%20has%20been%20stronger%20than%20they%20expected%2C%20long-term%20interest%20rates%20have%20fallen%20and%20the%20stock%20market%20has%20risen%20sharply%2C%20reducing%20the%20need%20for%20any%20early%20easing%20and%20increasing%2C%20in%20their%20minds%2C%20the%20risk%20that%20any%20such%20easing%20could%20restoke%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20added.%20%26quot%3BThat%20being%20said%2C%20data%20due%20this%20week%20could%20help%20trace%20out%20a%20likely%20path%20for%20the%20economy%20from%20here%2C%20providing%20guidance%20to%20the%20Fed%20and%20investors%20alike.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWh