er%20joining%20the%20Air%20Force%20in%201997%20and%20dealing%20with%20intense%20pain%20since%20basic%20training%2C%20she's%20struggled%20to%20maintain%20a%20job.%20She%20said%20it%20became%20too%20difficult%20to%20work%20consistently%2C%20and%20she%20needed%20the%20flexibility%20to%20work%20when%20she%20felt%20up%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20took%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-delivery-driver-tipping-millennial-doordash-gig-worker-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20driving%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%202023%2C%20hoping%20it%20would%20help%20her%20pay%20bills.%20However%2C%20increased%20competition%20for%20rides%20in%20her%20area%20and%20earnings%20that%20come%20in%20at%20about%20%2410%20to%20%2415%20an%20hour%20after%20taxes%20and%20car%20expenses%20have%20forced%20her%20to%20consider%20other%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20hard%20to%20say%20to%20an%20employer%2C%20'I%20can't%20sit%20for%20more%20than%20two%20hours%2C%20but%20I%20need%20to%20make%20a%20full-time%20wage%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20country%2C%20thousands%20of%20Americans%20with%20disabilities%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-many-hours-uber-lyft-drivers-work-taxi-competitive-inflation-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elooking%20to%20gig%20work%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAs%20many%20Americans%20with%20disabilities%20are%20unable%20to%20put%20in%2040%20hours%20a%20week%20or%20sit%20behind%20a%20desk%20for%20eight%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20many%20look%20to%20the%20flexibility%20of%20gig%20roles%20including%20ride-hail%20driving%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20work%20for%20a%20few%20hours%20a%20week%20and%20craft%20a%20schedule%20around%20medical%20appointments%20or%20recovery%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20many%20gig%20drivers%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fdisability-earning-saving-money-on-my-own-impossible-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20including%20veterans%20%E2%80%94%20aren't%20making%20enough%20per%20hour%20to%20pay%20their%20rent%20and%20car%20bills%20given%20gas%20prices%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20vehicle%20maintenance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20statements%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flyft-uber-gig-driving-with-disability-stock-flexibility-part-time-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUber%20and%20Lyft%20previously%20outlined%20their%20commitments%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20supporting%20disabled%20drivers%20through%20accessibility%20and%20antidiscrimination%20policies%20and%20resources%20for%20various%20physical%20and%20mental%20disabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20back%20into%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20heels%20of%20a%20divorce%2C%20Rene%20joined%20the%20Air%20Force%2C%20though%20she%20developed%20a%20back%20injury%20during%20basic%20training.%20She%20was%20able%20to%20work%20through%20the%20pain%20and%20became%20an%20active-duty%20member%2C%20though%20she%20said%20she%20faced%20harassment%20from%20her%20supervisor%20that%20led%20her%20to%20seek%20therapy.%20After%20her%20grandmother%20became%20ill%20and%20needed%20care%2C%20she%20left%20the%20Air%20Force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20she%20said%20she%20has%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20PTSD%2C%20REM%20sleep%20disorder%2C%20and%20sleep%20terrors%2C%20medical%20records%20shared%20with%20BI%20show.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EShe%20still%20needs%20to%20see%20a%20chiropractor%20for%20her%20back%20condition%2C%20which%20has%20been%20costly.%20She%20said%20she%20now%20has%20trouble%20digesting%20food%20and%20may%20need%20spinal%20fusion%20surgery%2C%20which%20would%20put%20her%20out%20of%20work%20for%20at%20least%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20at%20the%20point%20where%20I%20have%20spent%20all%20these%20years%20not%20being%20able%20to%20live%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Rene%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20do%20hiking%2C%20biking%2C%20camping%2C%20skiing%2C%20I%20can't%20do%20any%20of%20that.%20I'm%20in%20pain%20if%20I%20just%20stand%20over%20the%20sink%20to%20do%20the%20dishes%20as%20a%20single%20person.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERene%20was%20denied%20by%20the%20VA%20to%20receive%20disability%20compensation.%20Documents%20she%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20showed%20the%20VA%20couldn't%20find%20direct%20evidence%20to%20support%20that%20her%20injuries%20were%20service-connected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVA%20wants%20to%20ensure%20all%20Veterans%2C%20family%20members%20and%20survivors%20receive%20the%20benefits%20they%20are%20entitled%20to%20and%20our%20goal%20is%20to%20work%20with%20Veterans%20every%20step%20of%20the%20way%20to%20get%20to%20'yes%2C'%26quot%3B%20the%20VA's%20press%20secretary%20Terrence%20Hayes%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20BI.%20%26quot%3BService%20connection%20for%20disability%20benefits%20generally%20requires%20three%20elements%20%E2%80%93%20qualifying%20service%2C%20as%20well%20as%20medical%20evidence%20of%20a%20current%20physical%20or%20mental%20disability%3B%20and%20evidence%20of%20a%20relationship%20between%20the%20disability%20and%20an%20injury%2C%20disease%2C%20or%20event%20in%20military%20service.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20working%20in%20any%20job%20requiring%20physical%20activity%20is%20impractical%2C%20as%20she%20can't%20lift%20things%20or%20sit%20for%20too%20long.%20She%20worked%20as%20a%20real-estate%20investor%2C%20the%20director%20of%20operations%20for%20a%20brokerage%20company%2C%20and%20a%20business%20process%20consultant%2C%20though%20she%20said%20recently%20it's%20been%20too%20difficult%20to%20maintain%20a%20constant%20workflow.%20She%20quit%20her%20real-estate%20job%20since%20after%20an%20open%20house%2C%20she%20said%20she%20could%20not%20work%20for%20two%20or%20three%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20hasn't%20been%20able%20to%20find%20other%20types%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-make-money-gig-worker-uber-lyft-doordash-delivery-driver-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20fit%20her%20needs%2C%20even%20as%20driving%20becomes%20more%20painful%20amid%20headaches%20and%20back%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20life%2C%20no%20self-care%2C%20exercise.%20There's%20no%20time%20for%20relationships%20because%20your%20whole%20day%20is%20spent%20managing%20the%20pain%20and%20then%20trying%20to%20squeeze%20in%20hours%20to%20pay%20the%20bills%2C%26quot%3B%20Rene%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20she%20tried%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriving-for-uber-lyft-retirement-gig-workers-delivery-driver-rideshare-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egig%20driving%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20few%20months%20in%20Fort%20Collins%2C%20which%20she%20said%20was%20profitable%20but%20not%20as%20much%20as%20a%20full-time%20job.%20She%20recently%20started%20driving%20for%20Uber%20and%20Lyft%20when%20she%20felt%20up%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20uncertainty%20of%20knowing%20how%20many%20miles%20she%20will%20drive%20or%20how%20many%20rides%20she%20will%20get%20has%20been%20difficult%20with%20her%20disabilities%2C%20as%20she%20never%20knows%20how%20long%20she%20can%20drive.%20Typically%2C%20she%20can%20only%20drive%20between%20two%20and%20four%20hours%20at%20a%20time%2C%20and%20after%20a%20longer%20day%20on%20the%20road%2C%20she%20needs%20a%20day%20or%20two%20to%20recover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonuses%20have%20also%20been%20a%20challenge%20for%20her%20to%20achieve%2C%20as%20many%20require%20dozens%20of%20rides%20in%20a%20short%20time%20period.%20She%20estimates%20before%20taxes%2C%20she%20will%20pull%20in%20%24150%20to%20%24175%20after%20gas%20if%20she%20works%20a%2013-hour%20day.%20This%20excludes%20her%20oil%20changes%2C%20tire%20re