n%20for%20our%20future.%20Daily%20activities%20such%20as%20exercising%2C%20going%20to%20work%2C%20and%20eating%20healthy%20are%20often%20more%20tied%20to%20a%20desired%20future%20than%20an%20immediate%20preference%20%E2%80%94%20who%20really%20%3Cem%3Ewants%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20work%20out%3F%20The%20problem%20is%20that%20thinking%20about%20the%20future%2C%20full%20of%20uncertainty%2C%20also%20generates%20a%20considerable%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-fueling-gen-z-job-anxiety-stress-mental-health-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanxiety%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20to%20research%20the%20psychology%20of%20nostalgia%20more%20than%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20explore%20how%20our%20longing%20for%20the%20past%20might%20serve%20as%20a%20kind%20of%20defense%20mechanism%20against%20that%20anxiety.%20My%20hypothesis%20was%20that%20nostalgic%20reflection%20%E2%80%94%20looking%20at%20photos%20of%20past%20vacations%2C%20cooking%20an%20old%20family%20recipe%2C%20or%20rewatching%20a%20favorite%20childhood%20film%20%E2%80%94%20provides%20solace%20when%20people%20are%20fearful%20about%20the%20future.%20There's%20now%20a%20considerable%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0065260114000045%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eevidence%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20support%20this%20idea.%20For%20one%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2015-47828-001%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewe%20found%20that%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20people%20spent%20a%20few%20minutes%20thinking%20pessimistically%20about%20the%20future%20of%20their%20relationships%2C%20they%20felt%20more%20nostalgic.%20We've%20also%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2006-20034-013%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enews%20stories%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20natural%20disasters%20sparked%20negative%20emotions%2C%20which%20then%20increased%20feelings%20of%20nostalgia.%20In%20survey%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1002%2Fejsp.2073%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20people%20reported%20feeling%20more%20nostalgic%20for%20the%20past%20when%20they%20were%20going%20through%20difficult%20events%20that%20threatened%20their%20well-being%20and%20made%20the%20future%20look%20dark%20%E2%80%94%20things%20like%20losing%20a%20job%2C%20being%20in%20poor%20health%2C%20going%20through%20a%20divorce%2C%20and%20grieving%20the%20death%20of%20a%20loved%20one.%20When%20people%20are%20worried%20about%20the%20future%2C%20and%20when%20they're%20experiencing%20distress%20in%20the%20present%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20become%20more%20nostalgic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20does%20nostalgia%20keep%20people%20stuck%20in%20the%20past%3F%20When%20we%20looked%20at%20the%20connection%20between%20nostalgia%20and%20loneliness%2C%20we%20found%20that%20it%20didn't.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-9280.2008.02194.x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EStudies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicate%20that%20feeling%20lonely%20increases%20nostalgia%20and%20that%20nostalgia%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20increases%20feelings%20of%20social%20connectedness.%20In%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2015-47828-001%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexperiment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20we%20conducted%2C%20participants%20were%20randomly%20assigned%20to%20spend%20a%20few%20minutes%20thinking%20about%20a%20memory%20that%20made%20them%20feel%20a%20sentimental%20longing%20for%20the%20past%20or%20a%20memory%20of%20an%20experience%20they%20considered%20typical.%20We%20then%20asked%20them%20how%20confident%20or%20motivated%20they%20felt%20to%20achieve%20social%20goals%2C%20solve%20relationship%20problem%20scenarios%2C%20or%20meet%20new%20people.%20The%20participants%20who'd%20thought%20of%20a%20nostalgic%20memory%20felt%20more%20confident%20about%20achieving%20social%20goals%20and%20solving%20relationship%20problems%20and%20were%20more%20motivated%20to%20pursue%20their%20social%20goals%20than%20those%20who'd%20thought%20of%20an%20ordinary%20memory.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20nostalgia%20doesn't%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2015-47828-001%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eease%20the%20pain%20of%20loneliness%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20it%20helps%20people%20resolve%20it%20and%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20broadly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS2352250X22002585%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2006-20034-013%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20nostalgic%20reflection%20increases%20feelings%20of%20inspiration%2C%20encourages%20an%20optimistic%20attitude%20about%20the%20future%2C%20improves%20self-esteem%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-to-amplify-creativity-marketing-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboosts%20creativity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20fosters%20the%20motivation%20to%20pursue%20important%20life%20goals.%20Thinking%20about%20cherished%20experiences%20that%20have%20made%20our%20lives%20fulfilling%20can%20help%20elevate%20our%20sense%20of%20meaning%20and%20energize%20us%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20focus%2C%20agency%2C%20and%20generosity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20nostalgia%20can%20help%20us%20move%20forward%2C%20it's%20also%20associated%20with%20failing%20to%20appreciate%20the%20ways%20society%20has%20already%20made%20progress.%20People%20who%20think%20that%20life%20was%20better%20in%20previous%20decades%20are%20dispositionally%20more%20nostalgic%20than%20those%20who%20have%20a%20less%20idealized%20view%20of%20the%20past.%20And%20a%20lot%20of%20Americans%20have%20a%20better%20view%20of%20the%20past%20than%20the%20present.%20In%20a%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F04%2F24%2Famericans-take-a-dim-view-of-the-nations-future-look-more-positively-at-the-past%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPew%20survey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2058%25%20of%20Americans%20said%20they%20thought%20life%20was%20better%2050%20years%20ago%2C%20up%20from%2043%25%20who%20said%20so%20in%202021.%20But%20having%20a%20more%20positive%20view%20of%20the%20past%20doesn't%20mean%20nostalgia's%20causing%20a%20failure%20to%20appreciate%20progress.%20Based%20on%20what%20we've%20learned%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0065260114000045%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epsychological%20causes%20and%20functions%20of%20nostalgia%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20likelier%20that%20Americans'%20dissatisfaction%20with%20their%20present%20circumstances%20or%20their%20anxiety%20about%20a%20changing%20world%20is%20what's%20causing%20their%20nostalgia.%20The%20nostalgia%20is%20a%20response%20to%20their%20fears%20%E2%80%94%20a%20defense%20mechanism%20helping%20them%20adjust%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20has%20different%20personality%20traits%20and%20experiences%20that%20make%20them%20more%20or%20less%20excited%20about%20a%20changing%20world.%20People%20who%20are%20always%20seeking%20out%20new%20ideas%2C%20experiences%2C%20and%20technologies%20are%20said%20to%20have%20high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FB9780121346454500329%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eopenness%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Others%20prefer%20stability%20and%20aren't%20enthusiastic%20about%20the%20latest%20trends%20and%20emerging%20possibilities.%20For%20those%20who%20don't%20love%20change%2C%20it%20can%20cause%20a%20lot%20of%20stress.%20And%20when%20people%20are%20uncertain%20or%20anxious%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20rigid%20in%20their%20thinking%20and%20more%20resistant%20to%20change.%20That's%20where%20nostalgia%20can%20help.%20By%20countering%20these%20negative%20emotional%20states%20and%20inspiring%20a%20more%20positive%20attitude%2C%20nostalgia%20encourages%20openness%20to%20change.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0022103115000116%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EStudies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%20that%20nostalgic%20reflection%20can%20increase%20openness%20to%20new%20ideas%20and%20experiences.%20Trips%20down%20memory%20lane%20may%20even%20play%20an%20important%20role%20in%20the%20development%20of%20new%20ideas%20and%20innovations%20by%20increasing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0022103115000116%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecreative%20thinking%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20even%20useful%20in%20the%20workplace%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Frecord%2F2016-51684-001%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EStudies%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%20that%20when%20employees%20spend%20a%20few%20minutes%20reflecting%20on%20a%20nostalgic%20work%20experience%2C%20they%20view%20their%20work%20as%20more%20meaningful%20and%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20want%20to%20quit.%20Critics%20of%20nostalgia%20likely%20don't%20realize%20that%20most%20people%20use%20their%20nostalgic%20memories%20in%20constructive%20ways%20to%20help%20them%20navigate%20an%20uncertain%20and%20dynamic%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Americans%20have%20a%20positive%20view%20of%20nostalgia.%20In%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhumanflourishinglab.org%2Fnostalgia-in-america%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurvey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20our%20team%20at%20Archbridge%20Institute's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhumanflourishinglab.org%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHuman%20Flourishing%20Lab%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2084%25%20of%20Americans%20agreed%20that%20their%20nostalgic%20memories%20served%20as%20a%20reminder%20of%20what's%20most%20important%20to%20them%2C%2072%25%20reported%20that%20nostalgic%20memories%20were%20a%20source%20of%20inspiration%20when%20life%20is%20difficult%20or%20uncertain%2C%20and%20nearly%2060%25%20said%20nostalgic%20memories%20offered%20guidance%20when%20they're%20unsure%20of%20which%20direction%20to%20take.%20Americans%2045%20and%20older%20were%20more%20likely%20than%20those%20under%2045%20to%20view%20nostalgic%20memories%20as%20reminders%20of%20what's%20important%20and%20as%20sources%20of%20inspiration%20and%20guidance.%20That%20isn't%20surprising%3B%20older%20adults%20have%20more%20life%20experiences%20to%20draw%20from.%20However%2C%20our%20survey%20found%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20American%20adults%20in%20every%20age%20group%20shared%20this%20positive%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20future-oriented%20view%20of%20nostalgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20new%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BPast%20Forward%3A%20How%20Nostalgia%20Can%20Help%20You%20Live%20a%20More%20Meaningful%20Life%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20explain%20that%20people%20can%20harness%20the%20power%20of%20nostalgia%20by%20examining%20their%20own%20nostalgia.%20If%20you%20find%20yourself%20thinking%20the%20past%20was%20generally%20better%20than%20the%20present%2C%20try%20writing%20down%20the%20specific%20aspects%20you%20think%20were%20superior%20%E2%80%94%20why%20do%20you%20think%20they%20were%20better%3F%20I've%20talked%20to%20numerous%20entrepreneurs%20and%20artists%20striving%20to%20create%20something%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-innovation-collaboration-return-to-office-work-from-home-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunique%20and%20innova